SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1.1 "Software" means the DeltaDatabase source code, compiled binaries,
    documentation, schemas, configuration files, and any other materials
    distributed under this License.

1.2 "Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the
    Software, including modifications, adaptations, translations, ports,
    forks, or any other form of transformation that incorporates all or a
    substantial portion of the Software.

1.3 "Licensee" means any individual or legal entity exercising rights granted
    by this License.

1.4 "Commercial Use" means use of the Software in connection with a business
    activity, including internal operations, provision of services to third
    parties, or integration into commercial products, regardless of whether
    direct revenue is generated from the Software itself.

1.5 "Qualifying Charity" means any registered, tax-exempt, non-profit
    organization whose primary mission is the support of one or more of the
    following causes:
    (a) Palestinian humanitarian aid or civil rights;
    (b) Transgender rights or gender-affirming care;
    (c) LGBTQ+ rights, equality, or welfare;
    (d) Ukrainian humanitarian aid, reconstruction, or civil rights.

1.6 "Restricted Government or Funding Source" means:
    (a) The government of the State of Israel;
    (b) The government of the Russian Federation;
    (c) Any state-owned enterprise, sovereign wealth fund, or governmental
        investment vehicle of either country listed above;
    (d) Any entity in which either government listed above holds, directly
        or indirectly, a controlling ownership interest (greater than 25%
        of voting shares or equivalent governance rights).

1.7 "License Version" means the specific numbered version of this License
    (e.g., "Version 1.0") under which a particular version of the Software
    was released.

1.8 "Covered Source" means any particular tagged release or published
    version of the Software together with the License Version under which
    it was published.

