SECTION 3 — CONDITIONS AND OBLIGATIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

3.1 License Persistence in Forks and Derivative Works.

    (a) Any Derivative Work that you distribute, publish, or otherwise make
        available to third parties MUST be distributed under this License,
        in its entirety and without modification.

    (b) You may NOT remove, replace, relicense, or sublicense Derivative
        Works under any other license, including more permissive or more
        restrictive open-source licenses, proprietary licenses, or any
        license that does not incorporate all conditions of this License.

    (c) Any attempt to distribute a Derivative Work under a different license
        automatically terminates all rights granted to you under this License.

    (d) You must retain, in all copies and substantial portions of the
        Software or Derivative Works, the complete and unmodified text of
        this License, together with a prominent notice that the Software is
        governed by this License.

3.2 Attribution.

    All copies of the Software or Derivative Works must include:
    (a) The original copyright notice;
    (b) A reference to the canonical location of this License
        (https://github.com/DeltaRule/DeltaDatabase/blob/main/LICENSE); and
    (c) A clear statement of any modifications made relative to the
        original Software.

3.3 No Misrepresentation.

    You may not claim that a Derivative Work is the original Software or
    that it was created by the original authors.

