SECTION 4 — ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The rights granted in Section 2 are available ONLY to Licensees who satisfy
ALL of the following eligibility requirements. An individual who is not acting
on behalf of a legal entity (i.e., personal, non-commercial use) is exempt
from requirements 4.2 and 4.3.

4.1 Absence of Restricted Funding.

    (a) The Licensee must not be a Restricted Government or Funding Source
        as defined in Section 1.6.

    (b) The Licensee must not have received, in the twelve (12) months
        immediately preceding the date of first use of the Software, more
        than twenty-five percent (25%) of its total operating funding,
        equity investment, grant funding, or any other form of financial
        support from any Restricted Government or Funding Source.

    (c) Any Licensee that becomes ineligible under this section after
        commencing use of the Software must cease all use, distribution,
        and modification of the Software and any Derivative Works within
        ninety (90) days of becoming ineligible.

4.2 Charitable Contribution Requirement.

    (a) To use the Software for any Commercial Use, the Licensee (or its
        parent or controlling entity) must have made a cumulative donation
        of no less than five hundred United States dollars (USD $500) — or
        the equivalent in another currency at the time of donation — to
        one or more Qualifying Charities.

    (b) Such donation(s) must have been made within the thirty-six (36)
        months preceding the date on which the Licensee first makes
        Commercial Use of the Software.

    (c) The Licensee must retain documentary evidence of the qualifying
        donation(s) (e.g., a charitable receipt, bank transfer record, or
        equivalent) and must provide such evidence to the copyright holders
        upon reasonable written request.

    (d) A single donation satisfies this requirement for all Commercial Use
        within the validity window defined in subsection (b). Subsequent
        uses that fall outside the validity window require a new qualifying
        donation.

4.3 Self-Certification.

    By exercising any right granted under this License for Commercial Use,
    the Licensee certifies that:
    (i)  it meets the eligibility requirements of Section 4.1; and
    (ii) it meets the eligibility requirements of Section 4.2.

    Providing false certification is a material breach of this License and
    results in immediate termination of all rights granted herein.

