SECTION 5 — NON-RETROACTIVITY OF LICENSE AMENDMENTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

5.1 Versioned Releases.

    Each publicly tagged or released version of the Software is permanently
    associated with the License Version under which it was released
    ("Covered Source"). The terms governing that Covered Source are fixed
    at the time of release.

5.2 Future License Versions.

    The copyright holders may publish revised or updated versions of this
    License in the future. Such revisions will carry a new version number
    (e.g., "Version 1.1", "Version 2.0").

5.3 Non-Retroactive Effect.

    A new or amended License Version applies only to versions of the
    Software released after the date on which the new License Version is
    published. No amendment to this License shall:
    (a) Retroactively alter the rights or obligations of any Licensee with
        respect to a Covered Source released under a prior License Version;
    (b) Invalidate or restrict any previously granted permission to use,
        modify, or distribute a Covered Source; or
    (c) Convert a past release from one License Version to another.

5.4 Licensee's Option on Future Releases.

    When a new License Version is published, a Licensee who has already
    accepted this License may elect to continue using any particular
    Covered Source under the License Version under which that Covered
    Source was released, or may choose to use future releases under the
    then-current License Version.

